@cygnus-x-1 agreed regarding the increase in memory footprint point.
So we have been using this convention is some classes and I was interested in continuing it 😄. The obvious benefit is that it is thread safe.
I think you will always need both (modifiable and unmodifiable) because if you were to only have the unmodifiable version available to the class then you can't add anything to it? If there is a way then happy to learn.
